quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  13,19,Is he who knows that what is revealed unto you from your Lord is the Truth like him who is blind? But only men of understanding heed
  13,20,Those who fulfil the Covenant of Allah and break not the pact
  13,21,"And those who join (attain) what Allah has commanded to be joined (attained), and dread their Lord and fear the woeful reckoning"
  13,22,"And those who patiently persevere, craving their LordÂ´s Countenance, and are steadfast in prayer, and spend, secretly and openly, in charity from what We have bestowed upon them, and overcome evil with good - these shall have the sequel of the final"
  13,23,"Gardens of perpetual bliss, into which they shall enter with the righteous amongst their fathers and their wives and their seed; and the angels shall enter unto them from every gate"
  13,24,"(With the salutation) \"Peace be upon you! For that you persevered in patience; and excellent is the sequel of final home"
  13,25,"And those who break the Covenant of Allah after ratifying it, and who sever what Allah hath commanded to be joined, and who do mischief in the earth - upon these is the curse of Allah, and for them is an ill abode"
  13,26,"Allah expands his bounty freely to whomsoever He will, or He restricts its measure; and they rejoice in the life of this world, but the life of this world is naught but a temporary comfort compared with the Hereafter"
  13,27,"Those who disbelieve say, \"Unless a sign is sent down upon him from his Lord....\". Say, \"Truly, Allah leads whom He will astray, but guides unto Him those who turn in repentance"
  13,28,"Those who believe and whose heart have rest in Zikr (remembering or mention) of Allah. Verily, in Zikr (remembering or mention) of Allah do hearts find rest (comfort, satisfaction, fulfilment)"